para_trans: All the schools of government and private management of survey medium in the state have decided to celebrate Republic Day with various activities from 26th January, 2025.
Government of Maharashtra
Department of School Education and CRODA
Government Circular No: S.No.364 / SD-4
Madam Kama Marg, Martyr Rajguru Chowk,
Mantralaya, Mumbai - 400 032
Date: December 31, 2024
Government Circular: -
The Constitution of India was adopted on 26 November 1949. Every year on this occasion
26 November is celebrated as Constitution Day. Constitution of India dated 26 January 1950
has been implemented since. Hence, 26 January is celebrated as Republic Day.
The day is a celebration of the country's independence and democratic values.
On this day, students take pride in the rich culture, history and future of their country.
It is very important to do. Accordingly, schools celebrate Republic Day on 26 January every year.
Hence, it is celebrated. By circular issued annually by the General Administration Department on the occasion of the Republic Day
Suggestions are given. The instructions in this circular should be followed first. The date with respect to compliance with these instructions
All media in the state will be private on Republic Day every year from 26 January 2025.
The following activities should be carried out by all schools of management. For this, freedom fighters from every village, ex
Activists of soldiers, public representatives, school management committee, teachers' parents' union and eminent citizens.
Take part.
1) Prabhat Pheri: After the flag hoisting in the school, students sing the national anthem, sing the national anthem, Indian
Read the Preamble to the Constitution, sing patriotic songs, and take a morning walk around the school premises.
Remove.
2) Speech Competition: Speeches on topics like freedom fighters, patriotism, democracy, etc. for students.
Competitions should be held.
3) Poetry Competition: Students write patriotic poems written by themselves or by other poets.
Read it.
Government Circular No: S.No.364 / SD-4
4) Dance Competition: A dance competition on patriotic songs should be organized for the students.
5) Painting Competition: A painting competition on patriotic themes should be held for the student.
6) Essay Competition: Essay writing competition for students on topics like patriotism, freedom struggle, etc.
to be organized.
7) Sports: A variety of sports should be organized for the student.
8) Exhibition: An exhibition of handicrafts, paintings, etc. created by the students should be organized.
The student's TST TA should be considered when organizing the above-mentioned events.
3. In this regard, the Republic Day shall be celebrated every year by the schools in accordance with the instructions in this circular.
Care should be taken by the Education Officer (Primary / Secondary), Education Inspector of the concerned district.
